" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "    " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "11.   " }{TEXT 
259 60 "Explain the meaning of the term \"floating point arithmetic.\"
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 80 "12.  \+
Execute the following command sequence and record any relevant observa
tions" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "convert(.333333333333
3333333,fraction);" "6#-%(convertG6$-%&FloatG6$\"4LLLLLLLLL$!#>%)fract
ionG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "convert(sqrt(2),fract
ion);" "6#-%(convertG6$-%%sqrtG6#\"\"#%)fractionG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "convert(evalf(sqrt(2)),fraction);" "6#-%(conve
rtG6$-%&evalfG6#-%%sqrtG6#\"\"#%)fractionG" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "12.  " }{TEXT 260 46 "This last \+
response is very misleading.  Why?  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 58 "13.  Experiment with several examples t
o determine if the " }{TEXT 256 7 "command" }{TEXT 261 29 " convert(ex
pression,fraction)" }{TEXT -1 68 "  is an \"exact operation\" or some \+
sort of \"approximate operation.\"  " }{TEXT 264 13 "Which is it? " }
{TEXT -1 25 "     Show your examples ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 24 
"14.  Continue as before." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "
Pi;" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "Digits:=100;" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "evalf(Pi);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 20 "convert(%,fraction);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "convert(%%,fraction,exact);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 127 "     Change the above number of digits to 10 and re
-execute the last three commands. Finally, change to 4 digits and reex
ecute." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 100 "15.  Pi is the numerical quantity and pi is the greek \+
letter.  The following sequence exploits this." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "pi=Pi;" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
